        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/e480ec/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-05-10T10:01:39.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello there, I dont know if there is still people here interested in this.</p>\n<p>Years ago I got some island models in 3DS format, from a project called LBANET. That project seems dead and I lost the copy I had downloaded.</p>\n<p>I found a program called lba2extviewer that can render all the 3d islands and it looks awesome. But there is no way to convert the models to a modern format.</p>\n<p>Id love to get the islands models to test an engine Im programming in C, or at least some info about the islands format to try and convert them myself.</p>\n<p>It would also be awesome to have lba2extviewer source.</p>\n<p>Thanks.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 8,
        "updated_at": "2024-10-25T15:28:30.976Z",
